  "notes": [
    {
      "label": "Why Boscastle",
      "text": "Flash floods are increasing with climate change. Boscastle is a flashy catchment. Steep slopes and slow draining geology cause rapid response, even from small, localised events"
    },
    {
      "label": "How it is observed",
      "text": "We use innovative remote-sensing techniques (LiDAR, ultrasonic altimeter, camera) to monitor flash floods in real time, capturing accurate data on their speed and intensity."
    }
  ],
